As of the [[2000 United States census|2000 U.S. census]], there were 12 people, five households, and five families residing in the city.<ref name="GR2" /> The [[population density]] was 11.8 people per square mile (4.5/km{{sup|2}}). There were five housing units at an average density of 4.9 per square mile (1.9/km{{sup|2}}). As identified by the census, no one in Weeki Wachee was [[Race and ethnicity in the United States#Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]]. All residents were [[Race and ethnicity in the United States#White and European Americans|White]] except for one [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] member of the [[Little River Band of Ottawa Indians]].

